
Overview of noun surge

The noun surge has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (4) rush, spate, surge, upsurge -- (a sudden forceful flow)
2. (2) surge, upsurge -- (a sudden or abrupt strong increase; "stimulated a surge of speculation"; "an upsurge of emotion"; "an upsurge in violent crime")
3. billow, surge -- (a large sea wave)

Overview of verb surge

The verb surge has 5 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (8) billow, surge, heave -- (rise and move, as in waves or billows; "The army surged forward")
2. (1) soar, soar up, soar upwards, surge, zoom -- (rise rapidly; "the dollar soared against the yen")
3. (1) tide, surge -- (rise or move forward; "surging waves")
4. (1) scend, surge -- (rise or heave upward under the influence of a natural force such as a wave; "the boats surged")
5. surge -- (see one's performance improve; "He levelled the score and then surged ahead")
